.so ../bk-macros
.TH "bk version" 1 %E% "\*(BC" "\*(UM"
.SH NAME 
bk version \- print \*(BK version
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bk version [-s]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The 
.B version
command shows what version of \*(BK you are running.
If the version is symbolically named (most are), the version will look
like:
.DS
\*(BK version is bk-3.0.4 20031218201658 for x86-glibc22-linux
Built by: lm@redhat71.bitmover.com in /build/3.0.x-lm/src
Built on: Thu Dec 18 17:32:47 PST 2003
.DE
.LP
The version output for a development snapshot looks like:
.DS
\*(BK version is 20040211171546 for x86-glibc23-linux
Built by: lm@work.bitmover.com in /home/bk/lm/3.0.x/src
Built on: Wed Feb 11 14:32:08 PST 2004
.DE
.LP
The timestamp value in the snapshot release is the time of the most
recent file modification within the \*(BK source code.
.SH OPTIONS
.if t .TP .6i
.if n .TP 1i
.B \-s
Print just the version number (either "3.0.4" or "20040211171546")
.SH NOTE
.LP
BitMover, Inc provides support for symbolically\-tagged version only.
The snapshot versions are completely unsupported.
.SH CATEGORY
.B Admin
.br
.B Common
